---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="What DonateCrate Accepts"
  description="See which clothing, shoes, linens, and bag-friendly household goods DonateCrate accepts for monthly pickup."
>
  <main class="simple-page">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Back to home</a>
    <span class="eyebrow">Accepted Items</span>
    <h1>Clothing, shoes, linens, and other household items that are easy to pick up and ready to go.</h1>
    <p class="simple-page__lede">
      Clothing and shoes are the most common items we collect, but they are not the only ones. If it fits in the
      bag, we are generally happy to take it. If it is more likely to break in the bag, place it in a crate or box
      and mark it clearly for DonateCrate pickup.
    </p>
    <div class="simple-grid">
      <article>
        <h2>Clothing</h2>
        <p>T-shirts, denim, jackets, dresses, kids clothing, and seasonal apparel that are clean and dry.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Shoes</h2>
        <p>Paired footwear in reusable condition. Keep pairs together so the pickup stays easy to sort.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Linens + soft goods</h2>
        <p>Sheets, towels, blankets, and similar soft household items that are dry, contained, and easy to carry.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Small household goods</h2>
        <p>Household items are welcome as long as they fit in the bag and can travel safely without damaging other donations.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Fragile items</h2>
        <p>If something could break in the bag, leave it in a crate or box instead and mark it so the driver knows it is for DonateCrate.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <section class="feature-band">
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">Best results</span>
        <h2>Bag items the way you would want to receive them.</h2>
        <p>Keep everything clean, dry, and contained so pickup day feels smooth and the items are ready for reuse.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span class="eyebrow">Not sure?</span>
        <h2>When in doubt, think safe, clean, and easy to carry.</h2>
        <p>If it fits in the bag, it is usually a good candidate. If it needs more protection, use a marked crate or box instead.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
